CatDescriptText: He is an enlisted man in the U.S. Army serving in the General Headquarters Reserve, possibly in the Coast Artillery Branch.  His ribbon may represent an American Defense Medal.
TitMainTitle: Portrait of smiling man wearing dark U. S. Army uniform, moustache, Coast Artillery insignia on lapel, and Headquarters Army Ground Forces and Army Ground Forces Overhead patch on shoulder, posed seated on rug covered bench, in front of moire background, in Harris Studio, another version
